Package com.gwtplatform.common.client

Interface Summary
IndirectProvider<T> Act as a Provider, but instead of returning the provided object, the user must pass a callback in which the object is handled.
 

Class Summary
CodeSplitBundleProvider<T,B extends ProviderBundle> Implements a IndirectProvider that uses code splitting for a specific type.
CodeSplitProvider<T> An IndirectProvider that gets the object using code splitting and invokes the callback once the code is loaded.
ProviderBundle This class can be used to contain a group of providers that should all sit behind the same split point.
StandardProvider<T> An IndirectProvider that immediately gets the object and invokes the callback, without performing code splitting.
